Name: Sounds Like Mario Kart
Description: Per league rules, this is drakirby's pick. Submit a song that could be in Mario Kart (but that isn't actually. Songs from Mario Kart are banned) And explain in the comments what type of track it would be on.

Name: Listen, I was 14, ok? (The Sequel)
Description:
For those of you who weren't here for the first-ever round of this league, let's try this again.  

Songs that you loved when you were 14... and maybe even still kinda love today.

Name: Non-English songs (The Sequel)
Description:
The rules: a few English words here and there are fine, but once you start stringing together more than a line or two of English at a time,  that's a DQ.

And Sigur Rós is banned.

Name: Alternate Reality Groundhog Day
Description: In the movie "Groundhog Day," the song "I Got You Babe" plays on the radio every morning Phil wakes up. What is a better song that could play?

Name: technically radio-friendly
Description: a great song that's technically radio-friendly but is actually dripping with extremely obvious innuendo

Name: Songs you try to convince yourself you can listen to while you write/concentrate... but you can't
Description: You really try to write or concentrate while listening to this song.. but you never can. Explain why in the comments.

Name: new song by an old band
Description: a good new song (post-2020) from a band that that formed before 2000

Name: friday songs
Description: this is just a fun one: a song you play headed home from a long week of work.

Description: Strong verse/chorus structure required and story about made up or real country it would serve in the comments
